definition: a picture or design printed from an engraving, put into print
details:
noun
- a picture or design printed from an engraving
- a fabric with a dyed pattern pressed onto it (usually by engraved rollers)
- a copy of a movie on film (especially a particular version of it)
- availability in printed form
= example: availability in printed form
- the text appearing in a book, newspaper, or other printed publication
= example: the text appearing in a book, newspaper, or other printed publication
- a visible indication made on a surface
= synonyms: mark
- a printed picture produced from a photographic negative
= synonyms: photographic print
verb
- put into print
= synonyms: publish
- write as if with print
- reproduce by printing
= synonyms: impress
- make into a print
= example: make into a print
